<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>

<activity xml:id="act-redondearHacerEstimaciones" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>[@@@@@@@@@]</title>

<statement>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li><p>Sample responses:</p><ul>
<li>I predict Andre’s total will be greater because his numbers will all be in the hundreds, even if the numbers are less than 100.</li>
<li>I predict Lin’s total will be greater because some of Andre’s numbers will be 0.</li>
</ul>
      </li>
      <li><p>Completed table:

</p><p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Table present.</p><table border="1">
<thead>
<tr>
<th scope="col">location</th>
<th scope="col">number</th>
<th scope="col">Andre's estimate (nearest hundred)</th>
<th scope="col">Lin's estimate (nearest ten)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>playground</td>
<td>94</td>
<td>100</td>
<td>90</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>cafeteria</td>
<td>163</td>
<td>200</td>
<td>160</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>art room</td>
<td>36</td>
<td>0</td>
<td>40</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>library</td>
<td>13</td>
<td>0</td>
<td>10</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>classrooms</td>
<td>216</td>
<td>200</td>
<td>220</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>gymnasium</td>
<td>109</td>
<td>100</td>
<td>110</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>music room</td>
<td>52</td>
<td>100</td>
<td>50</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>total</td>
<td></td>
<td>700</td>
<td>680</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
      </li>
      <li><p>Sample responses:</p><ul>
<li>Andre’s estimate is 20 more than Lin’s. My prediction was wrong.</li>
<li>Sometimes there’s no difference in their estimates, but other times they are different by 10, 20, or 50.</li>
<li>For two numbers, Andre’s estimate made it look like there were 0 people in those places (art room and library), while there were actually 36 and 13.</li>
</ul>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


